# Clamp Light Color Controller
entities.aonHelper/ClampLightColorController.placements.name.clamp_light_color_controller=Clamp Light Color Controller
entities.aonHelper/ClampLightColorController.placements.description.clamp_light_color_controller=A controller that limits the maximum allowed light color.
entities.aonHelper/ClampLightColorController.attributes.description.color=The color to clamp the light color to.\nThis means that all light will "cap out" at this color, e.g. if this is set to pure red (#ff0000) and there is a white light source, that light source will appear red instead.
entities.aonHelper/ClampLightColorController.attributes.description.clampMethod=The method with which to clamp the light color.\nClamp: no light values below the specified color will be affected, all light values above the specified color will be clamped to the clamp color (newLightColor = min(lightColor, clampColor)).\nTint: All light values will be modified such that white light will appear as the clamp color, and everything else will be darker (newLightColor = lightColor * clampColor).

